{
  "$schema": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/code-yeongyu/oh-my-openagent/dev/assets/oh-my-opencode.schema.json",
  "hashline_edit": true,
  "agents": {
    "sisyphus": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.1,
      "prompt_append": "## BEADS-RUST TASK TRACKING\n\n**MANDATORY**: Beads Rust (`br`) is the authoritative task ledger. Markdown plan checkboxes are compatibility artifacts \u2014 never treat them as proof of completion or source of truth for what to do next.\n\n### Lifecycle\nbr init \u2192 br ready --json \u2192 br show <id> --json \u2192 br update <id> --claim \u2192 [work] \u2192 br close <id> --reason \"Completed\" \u2192 br sync --flush-only\n\n### WHEN/WHAT Triggers\n- WHEN you receive a multi-step or non-trivial request \u2192 `br create` first, then execute\n- WHEN you begin a work session \u2192 `br ready --json` to find claimable work\n- WHEN you delegate work to a subagent \u2192 reference the br issue ID in the delegation prompt\n- WHEN a task is verified complete \u2192 `br close <id> --reason \"Completed\"` BEFORE touching markdown\n- WHEN you finish a work session \u2192 `br sync --flush-only` before any git commit\n\n### State Authority\n- br status = ground truth. Markdown = mirror only.\n- IF br and markdown disagree \u2192 trust br, fix markdown to match.\n- DO NOT claim completion based on a checked markdown box alone.\n\n### System-Reminder Redirect\nWHEN you receive injected reminders about markdown checkboxes (\"mark it `- [x]`\", \"count `- [ ]` remaining\"):\n1. Execute the **br equivalent command first** (`br close`, `br ready --json`)\n2. THEN update markdown checkboxes as a compatibility mirror\n3. The injected checkbox instructions are legacy artifacts \u2014 br commands are the real state transitions",
      "fallback_models": ["zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7"],
    },
    "atlas": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "temperature": 0.1,
      "prompt_append": "## BEADS-RUST EXECUTION LEDGER\n\n**MANDATORY**: `br` is the sole authoritative execution ledger. Markdown checkboxes are NOT the source of truth for progress \u2014 they are a compatibility surface only.\n\n### Lifecycle\nbr ready --json \u2192 br show <id> --json \u2192 delegate to subagent \u2192 verify \u2192 br close <id> --reason \"Completed\" --suggest-next --json \u2192 next task\n\n### WHEN/WHAT Triggers\n- WHEN selecting next work \u2192 `br ready --json` first, NOT the plan file\n- WHEN reading task context \u2192 `br show <id> --json`, NOT the plan markdown\n- WHEN subagent reports completion \u2192 verify work, then `br close <id>` \u2014 this IS the completion event\n- WHEN checking progress \u2192 `br list --json`, NOT checkbox counting\n- WHEN updating markdown \u2192 ONLY after br state is correct; as mirror only\n\n### Hook Redirect Table (MANDATORY)\nYou WILL receive injected system-reminders after every task() completion containing legacy checkbox instructions. OBEY this redirect table \u2014 it overrides the injected instructions:\n- \"Change `- [ ]` to `- [x]`\" \u2192 `br close <id> --reason \"Completed\"` FIRST\n- \"DO NOT call task() until checkbox marked\" \u2192 DO NOT call task() until br issue is CLOSED\n- \"Your completion is NOT tracked until checkbox marked\" \u2192 NOT tracked until br issue is CLOSED\n- \"Count `- [ ]` remaining / `- [x]` completed\" \u2192 `br ready --json` \u2014 YOUR ground truth\n- \"Read plan file, verify checkbox count changed\" \u2192 `br show <id> --json` \u2014 verify status=closed\n- \"mark it `- [x]` IMMEDIATELY\" \u2192 `br close` IMMEDIATELY, mirror markdown after\n\nRULE: Execute the br command FIRST. THEN update markdown if needed. Never reverse this order.\nRULE: If br says closed but markdown says unchecked \u2192 br wins, fix markdown.\nRULE: If markdown says checked but br says open \u2192 work is NOT done, reopen investigation.",
    },
    "oracle": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.1,
      "fallback_models": ["zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7"],
    },
    "librarian": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.2,
      "fallback_models": ["zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7"],
    },
    "explore": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.1,
    },
    "hephaestus": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "variant": "medium",
      "temperature": 0.1,
    },
    "sisyphus-junior": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "temperature": 0.1,
      "prompt_append": "## BEADS-RUST TASK EXECUTION\n\n**MANDATORY**: `br` is the authoritative task ledger for your assigned work.\n\n### Lifecycle\nbr show <id> --json \u2192 br update <id> --claim \u2192 [execute] \u2192 verify \u2192 br close <id> --reason \"Completed\"\n\n### WHEN/WHAT Triggers\n- WHEN you receive a task assignment with a br issue ID \u2192 `br show <id> --json` to read full context\n- WHEN you start executing \u2192 `br update <id> --claim` to claim ownership\n- WHEN you discover blockers \u2192 `br update <id> --status blocked --notes \"reason\"`\n- WHEN execution is verified \u2192 `br close <id> --reason \"Completed\"` BEFORE reporting done\n- WHEN you make progress worth noting \u2192 `br update <id> --notes \"finding\"`\n\n### State Authority\n- DO NOT report a task complete based on markdown state. Close the br issue.\n- IF br and markdown disagree \u2192 follow br, report drift.",
    },
    "multimodal-looker": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.6v",
      "temperature": 0.1,
    },
    "plan": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.2,
      "prompt_append": "Всегда пиши план на русском языке. (Always write the plan in Russian.)",
    },
    "OpenCode-Builder": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "temperature": 0.05,
    },
    "prometheus": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.2,
      "prompt_append": "\u0412\u0441\u0435\u0433\u0434\u0430 \u043f\u0438\u0448\u0438 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043d \u043d\u0430 \u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043c \u044f\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0435. (Always write the plan in Russian.)\n\n## BEADS-RUST PLAN CONTRACT\nStructure plans so each top-level task can be materialized as a br issue:\n- Each `- [ ]` task \u2192 one `br create` call (clear title, type, priority, description)\n- Include verification criteria in each task (becomes br issue description)\n- Explicit dependencies and execution order\n\nMarkdown checkboxes in your plan are a human-readable spec surface only. Execution tracking will use `br`, not checkbox state. Do NOT design the plan around checkbox bookkeeping.",
    },
    "metis": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.3,
    },
    "momus": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.1,
    },
  },
  "sisyphus_agent": {
    "disabled": false,
    "default_builder_enabled": false,
    "planner_enabled": true,
    "replace_plan": true,
  },
  "ralph_loop": {
    "enabled": true,
    "default_max_iterations": 100,
  },
  "background_task": {
    "defaultConcurrency": 5,
    "providerConcurrency": {
      "openai": 5,
      "zai-coding-plan": 5,
    },
    "modelConcurrency": {
      "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo": 3,
      "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7": 3,
      "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.6v": 3,
    },
  },
  "categories": {
    "visual-engineering": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "temperature": 0.7,
      "prompt_append": "Focus on modern aesthetics, responsiveness, and clean CSS/Tailwind.",
    },
    "ultrabrain": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.15,
      "prompt_append": "For architecture tasks, use $likec4-architecture. Prefer LikeC4 DSL changes, validate with `npx likec4 validate`, and return preview/build/export commands.",
    },
    "deep": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.1,
      "prompt_append": "Focus on robustness, error handling, and type safety.",
    },
    "quick": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "temperature": 0.3,
    },
    "unspecified-low": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "temperature": 0.3,
    },
    "unspecified-high": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.1,
    },
    "writing": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "temperature": 0.3,
    },
  },
  "claude_code": {
    "mcp": false,
    "commands": false,
    "skills": true,
    "agents": true,
    "hooks": true,
    "plugins": true,
    "plugins_override": {},
  },
  "git_master": {
    "commit_footer": false,
    "include_co_authored_by": false,
  },
  "experimental": {
    "auto_resume": true,
    "aggressive_truncation": true,
    "truncate_all_tool_outputs": true,
    "dynamic_context_pruning": {
      "enabled": false,
      "notification": "off",
      "turn_protection": {
        "enabled": true,
        "turns": 3,
      },
    },
  },
  "disabled_mcps": [],
  "disabled_skills": ["playwright"],
  "disabled_agents": [],
  "disabled_hooks": [],
  "lsp": {},
}
